# Frontend Testing Principles (For Planning)

When creating implementation plans, ensure they align with these testing requirements.

## Framework Requirements

| Purpose | Framework |
|---------|-----------|
| Unit Tests | Jest + React Testing Library |
| E2E Tests | Playwright |
| API Mocking | MSW (Mock Service Worker) |

## Critical Rules (Plan for these)

Plans MUST account for these patterns to avoid execution deviations:

| Rule | Correct | Incorrect |
|------|---------|-----------|
| User interactions | `userEvent.click()` | `fireEvent.click()` |
| Element queries | `screen.getByRole()` | `getByTestId()`, `container.querySelector()` |
| Async elements | `screen.findByRole()` | `waitFor(() => getByRole())` |
| Query access | `screen.getByRole()` | `const { getByRole } = render()` |
| Assertions | `expect(el).toBeDisabled()` | `expect(el.disabled).toBe(true)` |

## Test File Location

- All tests in `__tests__/` directory at project root
- Mirror source structure: `components/layout/header.tsx` → `__tests__/components/layout/header.test.tsx`

## When Planning Test Tasks

Include in acceptance criteria:

- [ ] Uses accessible queries (`getByRole`, `getByLabelText`)
- [ ] Uses `userEvent` for interactions
- [ ] Uses `screen` for all queries
- [ ] Includes loading/error state tests for async components

